race.comment: The $200,000 Listed Falvelon. HIDDEN WEALTH (1) returned in fine fashion with a strong win in the Swiss Ace before just missing the placings at G3 level last time out. Ready to find his best now third-up from the spell and will be right there when the judge calls a halt. FLEETWOOD (15) returned to the winners' stall at the Gold Coast last start and will have derived a bunch of confidence from that breakthrough victory. Can go right on with the job now. The well-related PEREILLE (9) (half to G2 winner Corniche) has hit the frame in both runs this campaign and only needs some luck from the wide draw to play a role in the finish. FIRE STAR (8) maps well for this from gate two and must be respected from the Snowden barn. Watch for sharp improvement. METALART (5) goes well for hoop Rodd who has only missed a drum once in nine steers. In the mix.
